The user's vocabulary, panic level, and mistakes must be realistic for this persona. A parent with a child will panic differently than a coworker. A hiker 2 hours from help will ask different follow-up questions than someone in an office with an ambulance on the way.

---
GENERATION RULES — follow every rule exactly:

CONVERSATION STRUCTURE — must follow this arc:
  Turn 1 (user): Opens in a panic. States the broad emergency but NOT all details yet. Voice must match the persona.
  Turn 2 (assistant): Stays calm. Asks 1–2 targeted clarifying questions (e.g., "Is the person conscious?", "How old is the victim?", "Is the bleeding controlled?")
  Turn 3 (user): Answers the questions. Reveals more details. Makes a common mistake reflecting their persona and knowledge level (e.g., tries to pull out an embedded object, applies ice directly to a burn).
  Turn 4 (assistant): Corrects the mistake. Gives the first concrete action step. Asks follow-up if needed.
  Turn 5+ (user/assistant): Continues until the procedure is complete or the user is told to call AMBULANCE. If time_pressure indicates help is far away, the assistant must prioritize what to do while waiting.

ASSISTANT BEHAVIOR RULES:
  a. Never give all steps at once — deliver 1–2 steps per turn, then check back.
  b. Never say "Great!", "Excellent!", "Good job!" — use neutral acknowledgments like "Understood." or "Okay."
  c. All instructions must be grounded ONLY in the reference text. Do not add steps not in the text.
  d. Always include an AMBULANCE recommendation turn if the condition is life-threatening.
  e. If time_pressure is set (e.g., remote location), the assistant must explicitly address what to do while waiting for help.

USER BEHAVIOR RULES:
  a. User must sound scared, may use incomplete sentences. Panic level and vocabulary must match the persona.
  b. User must make at least one mistake (wrong action, misconception) consistent with their knowledge level and persona.
  c. User reveals information progressively — not all at once.

SKIP RULE: If the reference text is a table of contents, index, glossary, or has no actionable first aid procedure, output only:
{% raw %}{"skip": true, "reason": "<one sentence reason>"}{% endraw %}

